rules: Rule1: Under the condition that a conservationist is certified in a skill, if it is not the case that the conservation project is successful when the conservationist maintains a natural place, then the project experiences failed conservation.
Rule2: Either a natural place is destroyed by a disaster or the conservation project is successful.
Rule3: Whenever a natural place is protected by a barrier, it is not destroyed by a disaster.
Rule4: If a natural place is restored by a conservationist, then it does not get destroyed by a disaster.
Rule5: Under the condition that funds are allocated to a project, the natural place is protected by a barrier.
Rule6: Whenever a team is assigned to a project, the natural place is restored by a conservationist.
Rule7: Provided that a conservationist can operate a vehicle, the conservation project is successful.
Rule8: If a project is reevaluated by a committee, then the project is stalled.
Rule9: Either a conservationist has access to natural places or, if they have the skill of forest management, then they can operate a vehicle.
Rule10: Under the condition that a material is delivered to a conservation site, it has been transported by a vehicle.
Rule11: If a conservationist plants a plant, then the conservation project is successful.
Rule12: Either a conservationist plants a plant or they maintain a natural place.
Rule13: Under the condition that it is not the case that funds are allocated to a project or a team is assigned to a project, the project is reevaluated by a committee.
Rule14: If it is not the case that funds are allocated to a project or a team is assigned to a project, then the project is not stalled.

Rule15: Provided that it is not the case that a material is processed in a factory or, if a material is harvested from a plant, the conservationist does not have access to natural places, then a material is delivered to a conservation site.
Rule16: Under the condition that it is not the case that, if a conservationist is not certified in a skill, then the project is funded by an agency, the project is completed by a timeline.
facts: Fact1: A conservationist has the skill of forest management.
Fact2: A material is harvested from a plant.
Fact3: It is not the case that the project experiences failed conservation.
Fact4: The project is not funded by an agency.
Fact5: The project is not completed by a timeline.
Fact6: A material is not processed in a factory.
Fact7: A material is not transported by a vehicle.
